# @Progress Reimagined - Episode #3 ; Series at https://www.youtube.com/@ProgressReimagined
# Kathleen Podcast Substack at https://kathleeninweb3.substack.com


=Description=

"As our world faces unprecedented changes, renowned commons researcher and P2P Foundation founder Michel Bauwens reveals how societal chaos is actually birthing a new civilization. Drawing from decades of research in peer-to-peer systems, commons-based solutions, and decentralized networks, he maps out what's emerging and why there's hope in this perspective-shifting episode."


Watch to discover: 

• Why current chaos is a necessary transition phase
• How seed forms predict future societal structures
• The role of Web3 and blockchain in this transformation
• Why regenerative practices are replacing extractive systems
• How communities can thrive during this transition

MEMORABLE QUOTES:

• "Regeneration is the  opposite of extraction."
• "Hope with evidence gives you agency."
• "We need to move from efficiency to resilience as a civilization."

KEY INSIGHTS:

• How civilizational chaos creates opportunities for transformation
• Why peer-to-peer systems and commons are reshaping society
• Understanding "seed forms" as predictors of future systems
• The emergence of translocal collaboration and organization
• How Web3 enables new forms of trust and coordination
• The shift from extraction to regeneration in economic systems


